description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit an Occupational Therapist in our Older Adult Community Mental Health Team (CMHT).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for an experienced, motivated, and forward thinking Occupational Therapist, who is keen to develop quality services and best practice in older adult mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team provides a specialist mental health service for older adults across South Manchester working with people in their own homes, care homes &amp; other specialist placements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will manage a varied caseload, being allocated Care Coordinator/Lead Professional for both organic &amp; functional clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to perform the role of Duty Worker, completing Initial CMHT assessments for new referrals, work within a varied MDT and be able to establish positive professional relationships with external agencies, family and carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Lucy Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: lucy.smith@gmmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0161 219 2336&lt;/p&gt;
